# Clerk v6

ADR-004. Clerk holds identity. Our `users` table holds authorization.

## `auth()` is ASYNC in v6

```ts
// ✅ Always:
const { userId, sessionId } = await auth();

// ❌ Never (broken in v6):
const { userId } = auth();
```

If you see code without `await` in front of `auth()`, fix it immediately. This is the most common bug from agents trained on older Clerk examples.

## Resolving the current user

Use the canonical helper, do not roll your own:

```ts
// src/lib/auth/current-user.ts (canonical, do not duplicate)
import "server-only";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/db/client";
import { users } from "@/db/schema/user";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getCurrentUserOrThrow() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("UNAUTHENTICATED");
  const row = await db.query.users.findFirst({
    where: eq(users.clerkUserId, userId),
  });
  if (!row) throw new Error("USER_NOT_PROVISIONED");
  return row;
}
```

For optional auth: `getCurrentUser()` returns `User | null`. Use only for pages that render differently based on signed-in state, like the home page.

## Role lookups

Roles live in `users.role` in our DB. Never `publicMetadata.role` from Clerk. Clerk metadata is mirrored on webhook; the DB is authoritative.

```ts
// ✅
const user = await getCurrentUserOrThrow();
if (user.role !== "ADMIN") throw new Error("FORBIDDEN");

// ❌
const { sessionClaims } = await auth();
if (sessionClaims?.publicMetadata?.role === "ADMIN") { /* ... */ }
```

## Webhooks

Path: `/api/clerk/webhook`. Verify signature with `svix`:

```ts
const payload = await req.text();
const headerPayload = await headers();
const wh = new Webhook(process.env.CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET!);
let evt: WebhookEvent;

try {
  evt = wh.verify(payload, {
    "svix-id": headerPayload.get("svix-id")!,
    "svix-timestamp": headerPayload.get("svix-timestamp")!,
    "svix-signature": headerPayload.get("svix-signature")!,
  }) as WebhookEvent;
} catch {
  return new Response("invalid signature", { status: 400 });
}
```

Subscribed events at minimum: `user.created`, `user.updated`, `user.deleted`. Mirror these into the `users` table. `user.deleted` does NOT hard-delete in our DB — soft-delete via `users.deleted_at`.

## 2FA for admins

Admin routes (`/admin/*`) middleware checks `twoFactorEnabled`:

```ts
const user = await clerkClient.users.getUser(userId);
if (!user.twoFactorEnabled) return redirect("/m/2fa-required");
```

A Playwright test asserts this redirect happens. Don't remove it without a follow-up test.

